# Documentation Organization

## File Placement

All new documentation files MUST go in the `docs/` folder, not the root directory.

**❌ BAD:**
```
design-system/
├── NEW_FEATURE_GUIDE.md      # Don't create here
├── COMPONENT_TIPS.md          # Don't create here
└── ARCHITECTURE_NOTES.md      # Don't create here
```

**✅ GOOD:**
```
design-system/
├── README.md                  # Only exception - main readme
├── CHANGELOG.md               # Only exception - version history
├── CONTRIBUTING.md            # Only exception - contribution guide
└── docs/
    ├── NEW_FEATURE_GUIDE.md  # Create here
    ├── COMPONENT_TIPS.md      # Create here
    └── ARCHITECTURE_NOTES.md  # Create here
```

## Exceptions

Only these files belong in the root:
- `README.md` - Main project documentation
- `CHANGELOG.md` - Version history
- `CONTRIBUTING.md` - Contribution guidelines

## Existing Essential Docs

- `docs/MITOSIS_GUIDELINES.md` - Component development
- `docs/APP_INTEGRATION_GUIDE.md` - App usage
- `docs/PUBLISHING_GUIDE.md` - Release workflow
- `docs/PILOT_ROLLOUT.md` - Rollout strategy

## When Creating New Documentation

1. Choose descriptive filename (e.g., `TESTING_STRATEGY.md`, `DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md`)
2. Create in `docs/` folder
3. Update README.md with link if it's important
4. Keep docs focused and actionable
